{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f7880b35-eba3-48d5-9a08-426eff3b6f3b","content":"\n\nThe official MCP Registry is the **MCP Servers Directory** at [https://github.com/modelcontextprotocol/servers](https://github.com/modelcontextprotocol/servers).\n\nTo register your server:\n\n1. **Fork** the `modelcontextprotocol/servers` repo on GitHub.\n2. **Add your server** to the community servers list in `README.md` (or the appropriate registry file — check their current contribution format).\n3. **Open a Pull Request** with:\n   - Server name & description\n   - Link to your NuGet package\n   - Installation/usage instructions\n   - What tools/resources it exposes\n\nBefore submitting, check their **CONTRIBUTING.md** for the latest submission guidelines, as the format evolves.\n\nYou can quickly review the current structure with:\n\n```bash\ngh repo view modelcontextprotocol/servers --web\n```\n\n> **Tip:** There's also a newer registry effort at [registry.modelcontextprotocol.io](https://registry.modelcontextprotocol.io) — worth checking if they now accept direct submissions via a JSON manifest or API.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"98611b73-dc60-4b96-a54c-9255f2c258d9","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to register their C# MCP server in the official MCP Registry. This is a knowledge question about the MCP (Model Context Protocol) ecosystem. Let me look up the current information about the MCP Registry.","outputTokens":328},"id":"b8e2f2fa-c627-4607-ae9d-ee0fa86ad024","timestamp":"2026-04-04T00:43:27.085Z","parentId":"877ebcb3-d7ff-4969-9d4d-da729c97660d"}
